    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2604.21968v1</id>
    <title>Gradient-Produced Neutrinos</title>
    <updated>2026-04-23T18:00:00Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.21968v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2604.21968v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>Sufficiently strong electric fields can produce charged-particle pairs via the Schwinger effect. We argue that steep matter-density gradients, as can arise in neutron star interiors, would analogously produce neutrino-antineutrino pairs. We then discuss observational signatures of these gradient-produced (anti)neutrinos and how they could provide new probes of neutron-star structure and baryon-dense QCD.</summary>
